  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-04-25 01:05 UTC \u2014 [P3: Strategy Development] Add a Confirmation Guardrail to the Funding Squeeze Detector So It Stops Boosting PM Confidence on Mixed Crowding Signals That Look Strong by Score but Conflict Internally\n\n**Task:** Review the live funding squeeze logic, compare its current output against the actual crowding inputs, and patch the detector if it is over-trusting single-source strength.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- Live detector snapshot before patch showed `SHORT_SQUEEZE`, score `96`, and `pm_adjustment=+0.10`.\n- But the internals were mixed, not confirmed:\n  - funding streak was strongly negative (`8` periods)\n  - long/short ratio trend was **rising** `+16.1%`, not falling\n- That means the detector was trying to boost PM bullish confidence from funding alone even while the crowding confirmation leg disagreed.\n- Patched `intelligence/funding-squeeze-detector.py` so PM adjustment only fires when funding direction and long/short ratio trend **confirm each other**.\n- Post-patch live output kept the high raw score but correctly zeroed PM influence:\n  - `direction=SHORT_SQUEEZE`\n  - `score=96`\n  - `ratio_confirms=false`\n  - `pm_adjustment=0`\n\n**My thinking:**\nThis is the right P3 fix because the bug was architectural, not just analytical. A high score looked impressive, but the model was mixing strong funding with contradictory crowd positioning and still pushing PM confidence around. That is exactly how strategy layers become noisy and overfit. Raw signal strength should not automatically become trading influence when confirmation breaks.\n\n**Decision:**\n- Keep the new confirmation guardrail in the funding squeeze detector.\n- Treat unconfirmed squeeze states as research-only context, not conviction input for PM.\n\n**Next:** On the next P3 heartbeat, trace where `squeeze-funding.json` is consumed and verify no downstream component assumes every high squeeze score deserves a PM confidence adjustment.\n\n## 2026-04-25 01:03 UTC \u2014 [P2: Smart Entry] Recheck the Tagged PM Outcome Set to See Whether the Time Filter Is Carrying More Edge Than the Cooldown Gate and Whether 19 UTC Should Be Cut Instead of Trusted\n\n**Task:** Analyze the richer tagged segment of `polymarket-assistant/confidence_outcomes.jsonl` and test a concrete parameter idea using real outcomes, specifically whether `v5a` and the active hour filter are doing more work than the `v6` cooldown gate.\n**Finding:**\n- Both bots are alive.\n- The tagged April subset contains `28` trades with `v5a` and `v6` fields.\n- `v5a_pass=true`: `23` trades, `60.9%` WR, `+0.177` EV/trade.\n- `v5a_pass=false`: `5` trades, `40.0%` WR, `-0.229` EV/trade.\n- `v6_cooldown_pass=true`: `15` trades, `53.3%` WR, `+0.032` EV/trade.\n- `v6_cooldown_pass=false`: `13` trades, `61.5%` WR, `+0.188` EV/trade.\n- Hour split is the loudest signal:\n  - `11 UTC`: `57.1%` WR, `+0.107` EV\n  - `12 UTC`: `75.0%` WR, `+0.446` EV",
